  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nA followup to issue #8115, a user should be able to use Unicode characters for their display name (for the record, Discord and other messengers support this)\r\n\r\nCurrently this is restricted in 2 places using a regular expression:\r\n\r\nstatus-desktop, Constants.qml:\r\n```qml\r\nStatusRegularExpressionValidator {\r\n  regularExpression: /^[a-zA-Z0-9\\-_]+$/\r\n  errorMessage: qsTr(\"Only letters, numbers, underscores and hyphens allowed\")\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut also in status-go, messenger-identity.go:\r\n```go\r\nfunc ValidateDisplayName(displayName *string) error {\r\n...\r\n  // ^[\\\\w-\\\\s]{5,24}$ to allow spaces\r\n  if match, _ := regexp.MatchString(\"^[\\\\w-\\\\s]{5,24}$\", name); !match {\r\n    return ErrInvalidDisplayNameRegExp\r\n  }\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe former is easy to fix, using the newly introduced StatusRegularExpressionValidator, but the status-go counterpart's regex has to be also adjusted accordingly (e.g. using the unicode \"Character class elements\": https://unicode.org/reports/tr18/#General_Category_Property)\r\n\r\nAlso notice the frontend doesn't allow spaces, while backend does\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nUser is able to set their own DisplayName using Unicode characters\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUser is unable to set their own DisplayName using Unicode characters\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: master\r\n- Operating System: all\r\n\r\n",
